---
export const prerender = true;
/**
 * Custom CRM Development Landing Page
 * Keywords: custom CRM development, custom CRM software, bespoke CRM,
 * CRM for small business, no per-seat CRM, own your CRM code
 */

import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import FaqAccordion from "../components/FaqAccordion.astro";
import { createServicePageSchema } from "../utils/schema";

const title = "Custom CRM Development | Codebrand";
const description =
  "Custom CRM development that fits your pipeline — no per-seat fees, you own the code. We build CRMs and run our own. Get a free scoping call today.";
const keywords =
  "custom crm development, custom crm software, bespoke crm, crm software development, no per seat crm, crm for small business, own crm code, custom sales crm";

const serviceSchema = createServicePageSchema({
  serviceType: "Custom CRM Development",
  name: "Custom CRM Development — Bespoke CRM Software Built Around Your Pipeline",
  description:
    "Custom CRM development for businesses tired of per-seat SaaS fees and rigid workflows. We build CRMs that map to your exact sales process — contacts, pipeline, quotes, follow-ups, invoicing and reporting — with full code ownership and no per-user licensing.",
  url: "https://www.codebrand.us/custom-crm-development",
  image: "https://www.codebrand.us/photos/bannercodebrand.webp",
  catalogName: "Custom CRM Development Services",
  catalogItems: [
    {
      name: "Contact & Account Management",
      description:
        "A single source of truth for leads, contacts, and companies — organized the way your team actually thinks about them.",
    },
    {
      name: "Custom Sales Pipeline",
      description:
        "Stages, fields, and automations modeled on your real deal flow instead of a generic template.",
    },
    {
      name: "Quotes & Proposals",
      description:
        "Generate branded quotes and proposals from CRM data and track them from sent to signed.",
    },
    {
      name: "Follow-ups & Reminders",
      description:
        "Automated task reminders and follow-up sequences so no lead goes cold.",
    },
    {
      name: "Invoicing & Inventory Integration",
      description:
        "Connect your CRM to accounting, invoicing, and stock systems so records stay in sync.",
    },
    {
      name: "Reports & Dashboards",
      description:
        "The metrics that matter to your business — pipeline value, close rates, rep performance — on one screen.",
    },
  ],
});

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Can you migrate my existing data into the new CRM?",
    answer:
      "Yes. Whether your contacts and deals live in Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho, a pile of spreadsheets, or an old in-house system, we map your existing fields to the new CRM and import everything cleanly. We handle deduplication, field matching, and a validation pass so nothing is lost or mangled in the move. You review a test import before we run the final migration.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can the CRM integrate with WhatsApp, email, and my accounting software?",
    answer:
      "Yes — integrations are one of the main reasons to go custom. We connect your CRM to email (Gmail, Outlook), WhatsApp Business, calendars, payment processors, and accounting or invoicing tools so data flows automatically instead of being copied by hand. If a service has an API, we can wire it in. Need automation on top of those connections? Our team also builds AI agents and workflow automation as a dedicated service.",
  },
  {
    question: "How long does it take to build a custom CRM?",
    answer:
      "A focused CRM covering contacts, a custom pipeline, and follow-ups is typically 5–10 weeks. Larger systems with quoting, invoicing integration, and multi-team permissions run longer and are built in phases. We ship a working core first so your team can start using it early, then layer on features based on real feedback instead of guessing everything up front.",
  },
  {
    question: "Who owns the CRM and the code when it's finished?",
    answer:
      "You do — 100%. You receive the full source code, the repository, and the database, along with documentation. There is no proprietary platform holding your data hostage and no license required to keep using what we built. You can host it anywhere and have any developer continue the work later.",
  },
  {
    question: "Do you charge per user, like Salesforce or HubSpot?",
    answer:
      "No. That's the core advantage of a custom CRM. Per-seat SaaS bills you more every time you add a salesperson, so the tool gets more expensive exactly as you grow. Your custom CRM has no per-user fee — add ten users or a hundred and your software cost doesn't change. You pay to build it once and to host it, nothing per head.",
  },
  {
    question: "Why should Codebrand build our CRM?",
    answer:
      "Because we run our own CRM to manage Codebrand's clients and pipeline, so we build these systems from the perspective of a team that actually depends on one daily. We know where generic CRMs get in the way and what makes a sales team adopt a tool instead of avoiding it. Founded in 2020 in San Pedro Sula, we're English-fluent, hold a 5.0-star Google rating, and build on React, Next.js, Node.js, Python, and PostgreSQL.",
  },
  {
    question: "Will my team need training, and do you maintain it after launch?",
    answer:
      "A custom CRM built around your existing process is far easier to adopt than a generic tool, and we provide documentation and a walkthrough at handoff. After launch we offer ongoing maintenance — security updates, fixes, and new features as you grow — or we can hand off cleanly to your internal developers. You're never stranded at go-live.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can it replace the several tools we use today?",
    answer:
      "Often, yes. Many teams run sales in one app, quotes in another, and follow-ups in a spreadsheet. A custom CRM can consolidate contacts, pipeline, quoting, reminders, and reporting into one system your team actually opens every morning — and integrate with the specialized tools you want to keep. Fewer logins, no copy-paste, one source of truth.",
  },
];

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faqs.map((faq) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: faq.question,
    acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: faq.answer },
  })),
};

const manages = [
  { icon: "👥", title: "Contacts & Accounts", desc: "Leads, contacts, and companies in one organized source of truth." },
  { icon: "📈", title: "Sales Pipeline", desc: "Stages and fields modeled on your real deal flow, not a template." },
  { icon: "📄", title: "Quotes & Proposals", desc: "Generate branded quotes from CRM data and track them to signed." },
  { icon: "🔔", title: "Follow-ups & Reminders", desc: "Automated tasks and sequences so no lead ever goes cold." },
  { icon: "🧾", title: "Invoicing & Inventory", desc: "Sync with accounting, invoicing, and stock systems automatically." },
  { icon: "📊", title: "Reports & Dashboards", desc: "Pipeline value, close rates, and rep performance on one screen." },
];

const comparison = [
  {
    label: "Pricing model",
    saas: "Per-seat fees that climb every time you hire",
    custom: "Build once, host it — no per-user charge",
  },
  {
    label: "Workflow",
    saas: "You bend your process to fit their software",
    custom: "The software maps to how you already sell",
  },
  {
    label: "Data ownership",
    saas: "Your data lives on their platform",
    custom: "You own the code, the database, and the data",
  },
  {
    label: "Features",
    saas: "Pay for modules you'll never use",
    custom: "Only the features your team actually needs",
  },
  {
    label: "Integrations",
    saas: "Limited to their marketplace and tiers",
    custom: "Connect anything with an API",
  },
];

const steps = [
  { n: "01", title: "Discovery", desc: "We map your sales process, pipeline stages, and the tools you need connected." },
  { n: "02", title: "Core Build", desc: "First sprint ships a usable CRM core — contacts and pipeline — for your team to try." },
  { n: "03", title: "Iterate in Sprints", desc: "Quotes, follow-ups, integrations, and reports added in short sprints on real feedback." },
  { n: "04", title: "Launch & Handoff", desc: "Data migration, training, and full code ownership. Maintenance if you want it." },
];

const rates = [
  { role: "Mid Developer", price: "$45", desc: "Feature work, integrations, and day-to-day CRM development." },
  { role: "Senior Developer", price: "$65", desc: "Complex logic, data modeling, and integration architecture." },
  { role: "Lead / Architect", price: "$95", desc: "System design, migration strategy, and technical direction." },
];

const stats = [
  { value: "$0", label: "Per-Seat Fees" },
  { value: "100%", label: "Code Ownership" },
  { value: "5.0★", label: "Google Rating" },
  { value: "Own", label: "CRM We Run" },
];
---

<Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  keywords={keywords}
  canonicalOverride="https://www.codebrand.us/custom-crm-development"
  breadcrumbNames={{ "custom-crm-development": "Custom CRM Development" }}
>
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />
  <script is:inline type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative bg-slate-950 pt-32 sm:pt-36 lg:pt-28 pb-16 sm:pb-20 lg:pb-28 font-poppins overflow-hidden">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative">
      <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-cyan-500/10 text-cyan-400 text-sm font-semibold rounded-full mb-6">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-cyan-400 animate-pulse"></span>
          Custom CRM Development
        </span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-white mb-6 leading-tight">
          Custom <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-orange-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent">CRM</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-slate-300 mb-10 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          A CRM shaped around your pipeline — not a rented one that charges
          per seat and forces its workflow on you. Build it once, own it forever.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mb-16">
          <a href="/contact" data-magnetic data-magnetic-strength="0.4" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-orange-600 hover:from-orange-600 hover:to-orange-700 text-white rounded-2xl font-semibold text-lg shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
            Scope Your CRM
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path></svg>
          </a>
          <a href="#compare" data-magnetic data-magnetic-strength="0.3" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 border border-white/20 hover:border-white/40 text-white rounded-2xl font-semibold text-lg transition-all duration-300">
            Custom vs SaaS
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
          {stats.map((stat) => (
            <div class="text-center p-6 bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-2xl">
              <div class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-orange-500">{stat.value}</div>
              <div class="text-slate-400 text-sm mt-2">{stat.label}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-white font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8" data-anim="heading">Stop renting your sales system</h2>
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700 space-y-6" data-anim="fade" data-delay="0.1">
        <p>
          Salesforce, HubSpot, and Zoho are powerful — but they bill you per user, so the tool gets more expensive every time you hire a rep. They also expect you to run your sales the way <em>they</em> designed it, which means paying for modules you never touch while working around the gaps that don't fit. For a lot of teams, that trade stops making sense.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-slate-900">A custom CRM flips it.</strong> The software maps to your pipeline, your stages, and your fields — not a generic template. There are no per-seat fees, so headcount growth doesn't inflate your software bill. And you own 100% of the code and the database, hosted wherever you want. Custom CRM work is a focused slice of our broader <a href="/custom-software-development" class="text-cyan-600 hover:text-cyan-700 font-semibold">custom software development</a> practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Codebrand builds on React, Next.js, Node.js, Python, and PostgreSQL, and we run our own CRM to manage clients and pipeline — so we build these tools as a team that lives in one daily. Explore how we work through our <a href="/nearshore-development" class="text-cyan-600 hover:text-cyan-700 font-semibold">nearshore development</a> model, or scale delivery with a <a href="/dedicated-development-team" class="text-cyan-600 hover:text-cyan-700 font-semibold">dedicated development team</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Section -->
  <section id="compare" class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-slate-50 font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" data-anim="heading">
          Custom CRM vs <span class="text-orange-500">Off-the-Shelf</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">Where a bespoke CRM pulls ahead of per-seat SaaS.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-4" data-anim="fade">
        <div class="hidden md:grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 px-6 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">
          <div></div>
          <div>Off-the-Shelf SaaS</div>
          <div>Your Custom CRM</div>
        </div>
        {comparison.map((row) => (
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 md:gap-4 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-slate-200 p-6">
            <div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">{row.label}</div>
            <div class="text-slate-500 flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-slate-300">✕</span>{row.saas}
            </div>
            <div class="text-slate-800 flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-orange-500">✓</span>{row.custom}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What It Manages Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-white font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" data-anim="heading">
          What Your CRM Can <span class="text-orange-500">Manage</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8" data-anim="fade">
        {manages.map((m) => (
          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-slate-200 hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300">
            <div class="text-4xl mb-4">{m.icon}</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">{m.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">{m.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Process Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-slate-50 font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" data-anim="heading">
          How We <span class="text-orange-500">Build It</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">Short sprints, working software early, no big-bang gamble.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8" data-anim="fade">
        {steps.map((step) => (
          <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-6 border border-slate-200">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-orange-500 mb-3">{step.n}</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">{step.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-600">{step.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Rates Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-white font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" data-anim="heading">
          Simple Hourly <span class="text-orange-500">Rates</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">Nearshore engineering in US Central Time — senior talent without the US price tag.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8" data-anim="fade">
        {rates.map((rate) => (
          <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8 border border-slate-200 text-center hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-2">{rate.role}</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-orange-500 mb-1">{rate.price}<span class="text-lg text-slate-400 font-medium">/hr</span></div>
            <p class="text-slate-600 mt-4">{rate.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-slate-50 font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" data-anim="heading">
          Custom CRM <span class="text-orange-500">FAQ</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <FaqAccordion faqs={faqs} />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-28 bg-slate-950 font-poppins">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6" data-anim="heading">
        Ready to own your <span class="text-orange-400">CRM?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 mb-10" data-anim="fade" data-delay="0.1">Free scoping call. Tell us how your team sells and we'll map a CRM to it.</p>
      <a href="/contact" data-magnetic data-magnetic-strength="0.4" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-10 py-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-orange-600 hover:from-orange-600 hover:to-orange-700 text-white rounded-2xl font-semibold text-lg shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
        Get Started
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6"></path></svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
